<div class="container faq-section">
    <h2 class="text-center mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)</h2>

    <!-- FAQ Item 1 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>1. What is mental health?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Mental health includes our emotional, psychological, and social well-being. It affects how we think, feel, and act. It also helps determine how we handle stress, relate to others, and make healthy choices.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 2 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>2. What are the signs of mental health problems?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Common signs include feeling sad or down, confused thinking, excessive fears or worries, extreme mood changes, and withdrawal from social activities.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 3 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>3. Can mental health problems be treated?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes, mental health problems are treatable. Many people with mental health problems recover fully or can manage their symptoms with therapy, medication, or a combination of treatments.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 4 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>4. How can I take care of my mental health?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Engage in physical activity, connect with loved ones, manage stress, practice mindfulness, and seek professional help when needed.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 5 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>5. What is therapy?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Therapy, also known as counseling, involves talking to a trained professional to address mental health issues, emotional difficulties, or behavioral challenges.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 6 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>6. What is depression?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Depression is a mood disorder characterized by persistent feelings of sadness, hopelessness, and a lack of interest in activities. It can affect daily functioning.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 7 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>7. What is anxiety?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Anxiety is a feeling of worry or fear that is strong enough to interfere with one's daily activities. It may include physical symptoms like sweating, rapid heartbeat, or restlessness.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 8 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>8. Can children experience mental health problems?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes, children can experience mental health problems, including anxiety, depression, ADHD, and behavioral disorders. Early diagnosis and treatment are important.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 9 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>9. What are the benefits of meditation for mental health?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Meditation can reduce stress, anxiety, and depression. It promotes relaxation, increases self-awareness, and enhances emotional health.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 10 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>10. How do I help someone with a mental health issue?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Be supportive, listen without judgment, encourage professional help, and educate yourself about the condition. Avoid minimizing their feelings or experiences.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 11 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>11. What is cognitive behavioral therapy (CBT)?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>CBT is a type of psychotherapy that helps individuals identify and challenge negative thought patterns and behaviors and replace them with healthier ones.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 12 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>12. Can lifestyle changes improve mental health?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes, regular exercise, a balanced diet, adequate sleep, and stress management can significantly improve mental well-being.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 13 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>13. What is bipolar disorder?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Bipolar disorder is a mental illness that causes extreme mood swings, including emotional highs (mania or hypomania) and lows (depression).</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 14 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>14. How do medications help with mental health conditions?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Medications such as antidepressants, antianxiety drugs, or mood stabilizers can help manage symptoms of mental health conditions when prescribed by a doctor.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- FAQ Item 15 -->
    <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-header">
            <h5>15. Can stress cause mental health problems?</h5>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-body">
            <p>Yes, chronic stress can contribute to mental health problems such as anxiety, depression, and even physical issues like heart disease. It's important to manage stress effectively.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>




